   {:e #blake3 "55e5616465270241a7bc189960b5bd07915e9d4d94f729dc65f69863fe807e73" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Key finding: the codebase is remarkably well-structured. 38 internal packages with clear separation of concerns. No single package exceeds ~3000 LOC (consistency is the largest). The event-sourcing model (3-stream JSONL + deterministic fold) is real and operational. The materialize pipeline (fold.go) is genuinely pure — no system clock, no RNG, no environment access. The 5-tier contradiction engine (graph/SAT/heuristic/SMT/LLM) is ambitiously layered. The code-to-spec annotation bridge works. This is production-quality infrastructure for specification management.; Witness system (1445 LOC): Evidence-based proof receipts for invariant implementation. 5 evidence levels: test, annotation, scan, review, attestation (+eval for LLM). Record() creates witnesses with spec_hash binding (auto-invalidation when spec changes — APP-INV-041). Verify() does mechanical annotation proof by scanning code for ddis:maintains/implements comments referencing the invariant ID. BuildReviewContext() produces Gestalt-Theory-framed review bundles with code snippets (25-line radius). Check() validates all witness freshness. This is the link between specification and implementation.; Drift analysis system (1166 LOC): Measures three types of drift: (1) ImplDrift — spec-vs-implementation gap (unspecified, unimplemented, contradictions), (2) IntentDrift — intent-vs-spec gap (uncovered non-negotiables, purposeless elements), (3) ProcessDrift — methodology compliance (witness coverage, spec-first ratio, tool intermediation, validate gating). Drift is classified along 3 dimensions: direction (impl-ahead/spec-ahead/contradictory/mutual), severity (additive/contradictory/structural), intentionality (planned/accidental/organic). Quality breakdown decomposes into correctness/depth/coherence. Integrates consistency engine tiers 2-4 for contradiction count. Planned divergences can be registered to reduce effective drift count. RemediationPackage provides actionable fix guidance.; Potential issue: the search engine rebuilds the LSI index on every query (BuildLSI inside Search function). This is O(n*k^2) SVD decomposition per query, which will be slow for large specs. The index should be precomputed and cached. The FTS5 index is persistent but LSI is ephemeral.; Materialize package (2005 LOC): Event-sourced fold engine that replays JSONL events into SQLite state. Key invariants: APP-INV-071 (log canonicality), APP-INV-073 (fold determinism — pure apply function, no system clock/RNG/env), APP-INV-075 (materialization idempotency). Architecture: (1) CausalSort via Kahn's topological sort with timestamp tiebreaker (APP-INV-074), (2) Apply function as big type switch over 17 event types, (3) Applier interface with 17 methods for SQL mutations, (4) FoldWithProcessors adds stream processor observers (APP-INV-080), (5) FoldFrom enables snapshot-based incremental replay (APP-INV-095). The diff system computes structural equivalence (StateHash SHA-256 over content fields only, excluding metadata). Generic diffMaps helper enables per-table comparison. This is a clean event-sourcing implementation.; Session entity: :task/t-040dcc5a; Session entity: :task/t-e387819f; Architecture pattern: the Go CLI uses ddis:implements and ddis:maintains annotations in code comments (e.g., // ddis:implements APP-ADR-002) to create traceable links between spec elements and implementation code. The annotate package scans for these, the witness system verifies them, and drift detection uses them. This is a real working bidirectional traceability system. The annotation format is simple enough for any language (just comment patterns) but powerful enough to drive verification.; Session entity: :task/t-76ce6a16; Search engine (2163 LOC): Hybrid search with 3+1 signals fused via Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF, K=60). Signal 1: BM25 via FTS5 full-text search with glossary-based query expansion. Signal 2: LSI (Latent Semantic Indexing) with SVD-based dimensionality reduction (k=50 max). Signal 3: PageRank authority scores computed from cross-reference graph. Signal 4: Type boosting (invariants 1.2x, ADRs 1.1x, glossary 0.8x). Query expansion uses glossary bidirectionally: query term to glossary definition, glossary definition to glossary term. LSI vectors stored as BLOB in SQLite.; Session entity: :task/t-029104fc; 5-tier contradiction detection engine (consistency package, 3004 LOC): Tier 2 (Graph): Jaccard overlap on cross-reference reach sets + polarity inversion detection between invariants from different domains. Tier 3 (SAT): semi-formal expressions encoded as propositional logic via gophersat. Tier 4 (Heuristic): polarity/quantifier/numeric bound rules + LSI semantic similarity. Tier 5 (SMT): Z3 subprocess, semi-formal to SMT-LIB2 encoding. Tier 6 (LLM): Anthropic API as judge. 9 conflict types: governance_overlap, negative_spec_violation, polarity_inversion, quantifier_conflict, numeric_bound_conflict, circular_implication, sat_unsatisfiable, smt_unsatisfiable, semantic_tension. Results deduplicated per element pair, highest confidence kept. Key invariant: APP-INV-019 (zero false positives)." :op :assert}
